    <article class="glass-article">
        <header>
            <span class="category-tag">TED-Ed Science Transcript</span>
            <h1>Which type of milk is best for you?</h1>
            <div class="author">Jonathan J. O'Sullivan &amp; Grace E. Cunningham</div>
        </header>

        <div class="transcript-container">
            
            <div class="transcript-pair">
                <span class="en">If you go to the store in search of milk, there are a dizzying number of products to choose from. There’s dairy milk, but also plant-based products.</span>
                <span class="zh">如果你去商店寻找奶，琳琅满目的产品多到让人眼花缭乱。除了牛奶，还有各种植物基产品。</span>
            </div>

            <div class="transcript-pair">
                <span class="en">To turn a plant into something resembling milk, it must be either soaked, drained, rinsed, and milled into a thick paste, or dried, and milled into flour.</span>
                <span class="zh">要把植物变成类似奶的状态，必须经过浸泡、沥干、冲洗并磨成浓稠的浆糊，或者将其干燥后磨成粉。</span>
            </div>

            <div class="transcript-pair">
                <span class="en">The plant paste or flour is then fortified with vitamins and minerals, flavoured, and diluted with water. The result is a barrage of options that share many of the qualities of animal milk.</span>
                <span class="zh">接着，在植物浆或植物粉中强化维生素和矿物质，调味并用水稀释。其结果是产生了一系列具有动物奶特性的替代选择。</span>
            </div>

            <div class="transcript-pair">
                <span class="en">So which milk is actually best for you? Let’s dive into some of the most popular milks: dairy, almond, soy, or oat?</span>
                <span class="zh">那么，究竟哪种奶对你最好？让我们深入研究最受欢迎的几种奶：牛奶、杏仁奶、豆奶或燕麦奶？</span>
            </div>

            <div class="transcript-pair">
                <span class="en">A <span class="highlight-data">250 ml</span> glass of cow’s milk contains <span class="highlight-data">8 grams</span> of protein, <span class="highlight-data">12 grams</span> of carbohydrates, and <span class="highlight-data">2 to 8 grams</span> of fat. That’s approximately 15% the daily protein an average adult needs.</span>
                <span class="zh">一杯 250 毫升的牛奶含有 8 克蛋白质、12 克碳水化合物和 2 到 8 克脂肪。这大约是成人每日所需蛋白质的 15%。</span>
            </div>

            <div class="transcript-pair">
                <span class="en">Most plant-based milks have less carbohydrates than dairy milk. They also have less fat, but more of what’s often called “good fats.”</span>
                <span class="zh">大多数植物奶的碳水化合物含量低于牛奶。脂肪也更少，但含有更多所谓的“优质脂肪”。</span>
            </div>

            <div class="transcript-pair">
                <span class="en">Looking more closely at our plant-based milks, both almond and oat are low in protein compared to dairy. But oat milk is full of <span class="highlight-data">beta-glucans</span>, a healthy type of fibre.</span>
                <span class="zh">仔细观察植物奶，杏仁奶和燕麦奶的蛋白质含量都低于牛奶。但燕麦奶富含β-葡聚糖，这是一种健康的纤维。</span>
            </div>

            <div class="transcript-pair">
                <span class="en">Soy milk, meanwhile, has as much protein as cow’s milk and is also a great source of potassium. Soybeans contain isoflavone, which we now know has a much weaker effect on our bodies than estrogen.</span>
                <span class="zh">豆奶的蛋白质含量与牛奶相当，也是钾的极好来源。大豆含有异黄酮，我们现在知道它对人体的影响远弱于雌激素。</span>
            </div>

            <div class="transcript-pair">
                <span class="en">It takes almost <span class="highlight-data">4 square kilometers</span> to produce just one glass of cow’s milk, land use that drives deforestation and habitat destruction.</span>
                <span class="zh">生产一小杯牛奶需要占用近 4 平方公里的土地，这种土地使用导致了森林砍伐和栖息地破坏。</span>
            </div>

            <div class="transcript-pair">
                <span class="en">Dairy milk uses the most water — about <span class="highlight-data">120 liters</span> per glass. Almonds take second place at more than <span class="highlight-data">70 liters</span>. Soy and oats only require about <span class="highlight-data">5 to 10 liters</span>.</span>
                <span class="zh">牛奶耗水最多，每杯约 120 升。杏仁奶位居第二，耗水超过 70 升。而豆奶和燕麦奶仅需约 5 到 10 升。</span>
            </div>

            <div class="transcript-pair">
                <span class="en">Overall, each glass of dairy milk contributes over half a kilogram of greenhouse gas emissions, about three times more than plant-based milks.</span>
                <span class="zh">总的来说，每杯牛奶产生的温室气体排放超过半公斤，约为植物奶的三倍。</span>
            </div>

            <div class="transcript-pair">
                <span class="en">In terms of the health of our planet, there’s a strong case for choosing plant-based milks, particularly oat or soy milk.</span>
                <span class="zh">从地球健康的角度来看，选择植物奶（尤其是燕麦奶或豆奶）的理由非常充分。</span>
            </div>

        </div>
    </article>

